The ocean is ours: Bolivia, a landlocked country, hopes the court will open the way to the Pacific
Seamen patrolling a riggins-covered naval headquarters in La Paz.
Public buildings raise a blue flag.
Marine bases from Lake Titicaca to the Amazon are decorated with the motto: We have the right to the sea.
